# Database migrations

When changing the **Supabase / PostgreSQL** schema, do **not** edit `supabase/schema.sql` directly and do **not** apply DDL inline in app code or docs.

Instead, add a new SQL migration file in `db/migrations/`.

## Workflow

1. Create a new file: `db/migrations/YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_short_description.sql`
2. Put all DDL there (`ALTER TABLE`, `CREATE TABLE`, indexes, RLS policies, etc.).
3. Update TypeScript types and sync code in `src/` to match the new schema.
4. Mention the migration file in the PR / change description so it can be run in Supabase SQL Editor.

## Example

```sql
-- db/migrations/20260607120000_add_notes_to_workout_sessions.sql
alter table workout_sessions
  add column if not exists notes text;
```

## IndexedDB (Dexie)

Local IndexedDB schema still uses Dexie version bumps in `src/db/index.ts`. That is separate from PostgreSQL migrations.
